<h2><b>Funder and Publisher Data Requirements</b></h2>

<h3><b>Funder requirements for research data</b></h3>

<p>In March 2021, the Tri-Agencies – Canadian Institutes of Health Research (CIHR), the Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council of Canada (NSERC), and the Social Sciences and Humanities Research Council of Canada (SSHRC) – released the <a href="https://science.gc.ca/site/science/en/interagency-research-funding/policies-and-guidelines/research-data-management/tri-agency-research-data-management-policy">Tri-Agency Research Data Management Policy</a>  and <a href="https://science.gc.ca/site/science/en/interagency-research-funding/policies-and-guidelines/research-data-management/tri-agency-research-data-management-policy-frequently-asked-questions">associated FAQs</a>.</p>

<p>Across CIHR, NSERC, and SSHRC, the policy outlines research responsibilities related to research data.  Going forward, researchers may be required to:</p>

<ol>
	<li>Include a <b>data management plan (DMP)</b> as part of funding applications
        <ul>
            <li>Status: <i>Policy implementation started Spring 2022 for select funding opportunities, policy rollout ongoing</i></li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <br>
    <li><b>Deposit</b> and share (when appropriate) the data supporting research outcomes
        <ul>
            <li>Status: <i>Policy implementation to be announced</i></li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<p>The RDM policy applies to research funded by the Tri-Agencies, and applicable policy elements required are articulated in the funding opportunity details.</p>
<br>

